<HEADLINE>
2007 WORLD ROBOT OLYMPIAD TO BE HELD IN TAIWAN
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb 7 (CNA) 02/07/07  20:11:22 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 World Robot Olympiad will be held at the National Taiwan
University's sports center from Nov. 16 to 18, the head of the
World Robot Olympiad Committee announced in Taipei Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1000 players from approximately 200 teams, representing 25
countries, will participate in this year's WRO, the largest in
its history.
</P>
<P>
WRO Committee Chairman Norikane Kanai, who came to Taiwan to look
into related affairs, attended a press conference at the National
Taiwan Science Education Center where he announced the
competition's date and place.
</P>
<P>
Topics for this year's competition categories were assigned by
Taiwan, and a new college group was added to the original
primary, junior high, and high school groups.
</P>
<P>
Players in regular competition will design robots that simulate
the Ali Mountain train's z-line switchback movement; in doing so
they will come to know specific construction features of Taiwan's
mountain railways. Teams in the open category competition are to
create a "family robot" that increases the convenience of family
life.
</P>
<P>
Related activities  will be held in succession,  including
seminars, selection competitions in schools and regions, and a
final national contest.
</P>
